The Hotel is a Palazzo, we stayed in a very nice suite with views of the pool and gardens, classic style mixed with plasma and bang & olufsen music equipment (nice blend).	Lovely building with classic decoration, a lot of wood panelling and an elegant atmosphere that reminded me of the Quisisana on Capri.	The building and decor are coolly elegant, modern yet richly Italian in design and "feel".	5 star elegance here that some might find 'traditional' in style - but that I liked, as it had not succumbed to a 'contemporary' makeover.	Breakfast was good - usual continental style plus scrambled eggs and bacon, cereals, fresh fruit and champagne!